quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  42,32,And from His signs/evidences (are) the ships in the sea/ocean like the signs/banners
  42,33,"If He wills/wants He stops/quietens the wind/breeze, so they continue/remain still/fixed in place on its back/surface , that truly in that (are) evidences/signs (E) to every/each patient/endurer, thankful/grateful"
  42,34,"Or He destroys/perishes them because (of) what they gathered/acquired , and He forgives/pardons on much"
  42,35,And those who argue/dispute in Our verses/evidences know (there is) none from (an) escape/diversion for them
  42,36,"So what you were given from a thing so (it is) long life/enjoyment (of) the life the present/worldly life, and what (is) at God (is) better and more lasting (everlasting) to those who believed and on their Lord, they rely/depend"
  42,37,"And those who avoid/distance themselves (from) the great/magnified sins`/crimes` biggest/greatest , and the enormous/atrocious deeds , and when they became angry, they forgive"
  42,38,"And those who answered/replied to their Lord and they kept up the prayers, and their matter/affair (is by) consultation/advice between them, and from what We provided for them, they spend"
  42,39,"And those who when/if the oppression/transgression struck/marked them , they become victorious"
  42,40,"And a sin`s/crime`s reimbursement (is) a sin/crime equal to it , so who forgave/pardoned and corrected/repaired , so his reward (is) on God, that He truly does not love/like the unjust/oppressors"
  42,41,"And who (E) became victorious after injustice/oppression to him, so those no way/path (blame) is on them"
  42,42,"But the way/path (blame is) on those who cause injustice/oppression (to) the people, and they oppress/transgress in the earth/Planet Earth without the right/truth , those for them (is) a painful torture"
  42,43,"And who (E) became patient and forgave, that truly that (is) from the matter`s/affair`s decisiveness/determination"
  42,44,"And whom God misguided, so (there is) none from a guardian/ally for him from after Him, and you see the unjust/oppressors when they saw the torture, they say: \"Is (there) from a way/path to return"